title: Kazakhstan Three Month Interbank Rate
description: Kazakhstan Three Month Interbank Rate was at 10.50 percent on Tuesday November 8. Interbank Rate in Kazakhstan averaged 8.44 percent from 2004 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 24 percent in February of 2009 and a record low of 0 percent in March of 2012. The interbank rate is the rate of interest charged on short-term loans made between banks in the local currency. This page provides - Kazakhstan Interbank Rate- actual values, historical data, forecast, chart, statistics, economic calendar and news.
author: National Bank of Kazakhstan
